videoPlayer.attentionCue.message: By analyzing the lecture video, the postures and behaviors of students can be identified, such as listening, head resting on desk, etc.. The changing trends of students’ Head-Up rate and Head-On-Desk rate curves can reflect the changes in students’ learning status to a certain extent and provide certain insights for school administrators. Facing-Up rate: the proportion of students’ listening behavior to all behaviors. Head-On-Desk rate: the ratio of students lying on the desk to all behaviors.

videoPlayer.teacherBehaviorCue.message: By analyzing the lecture video, the teacher's instructional behaviors can be identified, such as lecturing, blackboard/whiteboard writing, etc.. The system can count the duration of each instructional behavior and its distribution throughout the teaching process.

videoPlayer.instructionalAnalysisMethod.message: S-T Teaching Analysis - Sampling and analyzing the instructional behaviors in the classroom. The S-T analysis can quantify instructional behaviors and deduce the classroom instructional model.

intelligentAnalysis.aiTip1.message: The results are generated by AI and are for reference only!

intelligentAnalysis.aiTip2.message: The large language model automatically generates a summary based on the teacher’s lecture content, allowing users to quickly understand what the teacher taught in the class.

intelligentAnalysis.aiTip3.message: Generated from a large language model - for reference only!

intelligentAnalysis.aiTip4.message:
The system can identify different speakers in the classroom, and judge various teaching scenarios such as teacher lecturing, teacher-student Q&A, and student presentations based on the interactions and behavior recognition among speakers.
Note: The duration of each instructional behavior is not equal to the total duration of the class.

intelligentAnalysis.aiTip5.message: The system identifies the instructional events conducted by the teacher at the current time spot through semantic understanding and keyword matching.

intelligentAnalysis.aiTip6.message:
The system uses the S-T teaching analysis method to analyze classroom teaching modes.
T means that the teacher's behavior is dominant at the current time, for example, teacher's lecturing. S means that students are involved at the current time, such as teacher-student Q&A, student discussions, and student presentations/speech. Conversion rate Ch = number of conversions between S and T / total number of samples.
Practice type: Rt <= 0.3
Lecture type: Rt >= 0.7
Dialogue type: Ch >= 0.4
Hybrid type: 0.3 < Rt < 0.7, Ch < 0.4

intelligentAnalysis.aiTip7.message: Teachers' Late/Leave Early: The system comprehensively judges whether teachers are late for class or leave early through multiple methods such as teacher’s teaching behavior and face recognition in the podium area. If the teacher is late or leaves early for more than {num} minutes, an alert will be given.

intelligentAnalysis.aiTip8.message:
The system can identify the number of students in the classroom (camera coverage area), count them once every minute, and generate a student attendance curve.
Actual attendance = peak number of students in the classroom
Absent = expected attendance - actual attendance
Late/Leave early = expected attendance - actual attendance 2 minutes after the class starts/before the class ends.

intelligentAnalysis.aiTip9.message:
The system recognizes students' behaviors through images, once per second. At a time:
Head-up rate = number of students (listening + raising hand + standing up) / total number of students
Reading/writing rate = number of students reading/writing / total number of students
Head-on-desk rate = number of students head on the desk / total number of students
Note: Some student behaviors may not be recognized or not counted by the system , head-up rate + reading/writing rate + head-on-desk rate may not equal to 100%.

intelligentAnalysis.aiTip10.message: The system identifies students' behavior by detecting their behavioral characteristics. The system identifies once per second and calculates the proportion of each type of student behavior. Note: Due to possible occlusion, unclear video, unclear behavioral characteristics, etc., there may be a certain error in behavior recognition. The analysis results are for reference only.
